---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy &#8212; Tango Garden"
  description="Privacy Policy (Datenschutzerkl&auml;rung) for Tango Garden Cologne, GDPR compliant."
  canonical="https://tangogarden.de/pages/privacy-policy"
  noindex
>
  <Fragment set:html={`
<div class="legal-page">
  <h1 class="legal-title">Privacy Policy (Datenschutzerklärung)</h1>
  <p style="font-size:0.75rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.12em;color:#6b6b6b;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Last updated: May 20, 2024</p>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>1. General Information</h2>
    <p>Protecting your personal data is very important to us. This privacy policy explains how Tango Garden ("we", "us") collects, uses, and protects your personal data when you visit our website or use our services. We process your data in accordance with the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR / DSGVO) and applicable German data protection laws.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>2. Data Controller</h2>
    <p>Responsible for data processing:</p>
    <div class="legal-box">
      <strong>Tango Garden</strong><br>
      Evangelos Theodorakis<br>
      Domagkstr. 6<br>
      51063 Cologne, Germany<br>
      Email: hello@tangogarden.de
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>3. Hosting &amp; Website Access Data</h2>
    <p>When you visit our website, the hosting provider automatically collects the following information: IP address, date and time of access, browser type/version, operating system, and referrer URL. This data is processed to ensure security and stability.</p>
    <p>Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest)</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>4. Contact via Email</h2>
    <p>If you contact us via email, we will store the data you provide solely for the purpose of responding to your inquiry. We do not share this data with third parties.</p>
    <p>Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>5. Booking, Payments &amp; Shopify</h2>
    <p>We use Shopify to manage bookings and payments. Shopify processes personal data such as name, email, and booking details. Payment processing is handled by Shopify's integrated providers; we do not store full payment details on our servers.</p>
    <p>Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR</p>
    <p>View <a href="https://www.shopify.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shopify's privacy policy here</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>6. QR Codes &amp; Attendance Tracking</h2>
    <p>Some products include QR codes to validate access (e.g., class bundles). These are used only to validate attendance and are not shared with third parties or used for marketing.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>7. Email Communication &amp; Updates</h2>
    <p>If you book a class, we may send essential emails related to your booking (confirmations, schedule updates). We do not send newsletters without explicit consent.</p>
    <p>Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR / Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>8. Photos &amp; Video Recordings</h2>
    <p>During classes, practicas, and events, photos and videos may be taken for documentation, marketing, and promotional purposes (e.g. website, social media). We make reasonable efforts to ensure participants are not portrayed inappropriately.</p>
    <p>Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent) and Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest)</p>
    <p>How to object: Participants may object to the use of photos or videos at any time by informing us on-site or by email at <a href="mailto:hello@tangogarden.de">hello@tangogarden.de</a>. We will respect the request and remove identifiable material whenever possible.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>9. Cookies</h2>
    <p>Our website may use technically necessary cookies to ensure proper functionality. We do not use tracking or profiling cookies without your consent.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>10. Social Media Links</h2>
    <p>Our website links to platforms like Instagram or Facebook. When clicking these, data processing occurs under the responsibility of the respective platform.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>11. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to access (Art. 15), rectify (Art. 16), delete (Art. 17), or restrict processing (Art. 18) of your data, as well as the right to data portability (Art. 20) and objection (Art. 21).</p>
    <p>Contact: hello@tangogarden.de</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>12. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We store personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill contractual or legal obligations.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>13. Right to Lodge a Complaint</h2>
    <p>You have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. In Germany: Landesbeauftragte für Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit NRW.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <h2>14. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy to reflect legal changes. The current version will always be available here.</p>
  </section>
</div>
`} />
</BaseLayout>

